<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="unless-conj">unless <strong><em>conj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ən'les/    美 /ən'les/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-if-not">1.★ <strong>除非；如果不(if ... not)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Unless the weather gets better, I’ll stay at home.
如果天气没有好转，我就待在家里。</p><footer>外研④ – 3</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He told me that I’d probably have a heart attack unless I started eating less.  
他告诉我，如果我再不减少食量，就有可能患心脏病。</p><footer>2005 广东</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>It is so cold that you can’t go outside <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ fully covered in thick clothes.  （2015 江苏）<br />
A.if<br />
B.unless<br />
C.once<br />
D.when  </li>
<li>You will never gain success if you are fully devoted to your work.  （2014 湖南改 改错）  </li>
<li>All the photographs in this book,<strong><em>_</em></strong>_stated otherwise, date from the 1950s.  （2012 陕 西）<br />
A.unless<br />
B.until<br />
C.once<br />
D. if  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. B  2. if → unless  3. A  </p></div>